1 (B) (1) THE EMERGENCY SERVICES TAX SHALL BE COLLECTED IN THE
2 SAME MANNER AS OTHER COUNTY TAXES ARE COLLECTED.
3 (2) IF A PROPERTY OWNER FAILS TO PAY THE EMERGENCY SERVICES
4 TAX WHEN DUE AND PAYABLE, THE UNPAID TAX SHALL:
5 (I) BE A LIEN ON ALL PROPERTY BELONGING TO THE PERSON
6 REQUIRED TO MAKE PAYMENT; AND
7 (II) ACCRUE INTEREST AND PENALTIES AT THE SAME RATE AND
8 IN THE SAME MANNER AS THE ACCRUAL OF INTEREST AND PENALTIES FOR UNPAID
9 COUNTY PROPERTY TAXES.
10 (3) PROPERTY MAY BE SOLD IN ACCORDANCE WITH TITLE 14,
11 SUBTITLE 8 OF THE TAX – PROPERTY ARTICLE TO ENFORCE THE EMERGENCY
12 SERVICES TAX.
13 (C) (1) THE COUNTY COMMISSIONERS MAY NOT ENACT A LAW TO
14 INITIALLY IMPOSE OR SUBSEQUENTLY INCREASE AN EMERGENCY SERVICES TAX
15 UNTIL AFTER A PUBLIC HEARING IS HELD ON THE PROPOSED LAW AT THE SAME
16 TIME AS THE COUNTY’S ANNUAL BUDGET HEARING.
17 (2) THE COUNTY SHALL PROVIDE THE PUBLIC WITH ADVANCE
18 NOTICE OF THE HEARING REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
20 1, 2025, and shall be applicable to all taxable years beginning after June 30, 2025.

